Defn.name: Description
Defn.val: The Renesas RA4L1 MCU group features low-power, 32-bit microcontrollers (MCUs) based on the Arm Cortex-M33 (CM33) core with TrustZone, delivering an ideal balance of low voltage operation, low power consumption, and high performance. The RA4L1 offers operation down to 1.6V combined with a low-power standby current of as little as 1.65A and a multitude of low-power features enabling the user to dynamically optimize power/performance to their application requirements.These MCUs include low-power features
